    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-07-20T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-07-20T06:00:00-05:00" n="561"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d561">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">785.00/7–2051: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Jordan</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_DGA1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Drew</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d561fn1">Repeated to Beirut, Baghdad, Cairo, Jidda,
                        Damascus, London, Paris, Tel Aviv, and Jerusalem.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <gloss target="#t_niact1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">niact</hi>
                        </gloss>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Amman</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-07-20T13:00:00+02:00"
                            >July 20, 1951—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>26. <gloss target="#t_Legtel1">Legtel</gloss> 25, July 20.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d561fn2">Not printed; it conveyed the following message to
                        Washington, repeated to Baghdad, Beirut, Cairo, Damascus, Jidda, London,
                        Paris, and Tel Aviv: King <persName corresp="#p_AH1">Abdullah</persName>
                        assassinated about noon July 20, at mosque Jerusalem.”
                        (785.11/7–2051)</note> Death of <persName corresp="#p_AAS1"
                        >Abdullah</persName>, mental condition and absence from country of Crown
                    Prince <persName>Tallal</persName>, and minority of
                    <persName>Tallal</persName>’s son <persName>Hussain</persName>, pose immed
                    serious constitutional problem regarding succession on which too early to
                    comment.</p>
                <p>Legion enforcing martial law immed. Police guards on foreign Legs being
                    strengthened. I am taking all possible precautions assure safety of Amer
                    personnel and residents and Leg property. Amer staff member will be on duty at
                    chancery 24 hours day. While confident ability Arab Legion maintain order I do
                    not exclude possibility disorders by irresponsible elements including refugees
                    with anti-foreign overtones.</p>
                <p>Have informed Amer Con branch [in] Arab-held Jerusalem requesting it do likewise
                    and keep Dept and me promptly and fully informed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DGA1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Drew</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
